radiator /ˈreɪdɪˌeɪtə/

(radiators) 

1. N-COUNT A radiator is a hollow metal device, usually connected by pipes to a central heating system, that is used to heat a room. 暖气片 

2. N-COUNT The radiator in a car is the part of the engine that is filled with water in order to cool the engine. (汽车引擎的) 水箱

